notes.text: AESIs = adverse event of special interest; anti-HBc = antibody to hepatitis B core antigen; DNA = deoxyribonucleic acid; ETV = early termination visit; HBV = hepatitis B virus; IT = information technology; NRS = numeric rating scale; QIDS-SR16 = 16-Item Quick Inventory of Depressive SymptomatologySelf Report; SoA = schedule of activities; V = visit.
V802 is only for randomized participants who were positive for anti-HBc at screening. All other participants will have their final visit at V801 or ETV.
V997: Additional study procedures can be performed at the discretion of the investigator.

Visits 10 through 28 are eligible to be conducted remotely (that is, by telephone, IT-assisted virtual visit, mobile healthcare, or a combination thereof) if written approval is provided by the sponsor and according to the preferences of the participant and the study site. However, no more than 34 days can elapse without an on-site study visit occurring.
V16 procedures may be conducted over more than 1 day as long as all activities are completed within the allowable visit tolerance and all scheduled activities are completed prior to dosing.
For procedures at an ETV, see ETV in Table 4.
For procedures at an unscheduled visit, see V997 in Table 4.
No dosing at ETV, V997, or post-treatment follow-up visits.

transitionRules.text: Study participants who are responders at Week 12 proceed to Maintenance Treatment Period

transitionRules.name: Induction to Extension Induction Transition (Nonresponders)

transitionRules.name: Extension Induction to Extension Maintenance Transition
transitionRules.text: Nonresponders continue from Extension Induction to Extension Maintenance Treatment Period

transitionRules.name: Treatment to Post-Treatment Follow-Up Transition
transitionRules.text: Post-treatment follow-up visits occur at least 8 weeks (V801) and 16 weeks (V802 if applicable) after last dose

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Early Termination Visit

scheduleTimelineExits.description: Participants complete study at V801 (Week 58 or ETV + 8 weeks after last dose) if not anti-HBc positive

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion - Anti-HBc Positive
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Participants positive for anti-HBc at screening complete study at V802 (Week 66 or ETV + 16 weeks after last dose)

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Week 52 End of Treatment
scheduleTimelineExits.description: No dosing at V29 (Week 52, Study Day 365)
